20#ifndef _ELF_MEP_H
21#define _ELF_MEP_H
22
23/* Bits in the sh_flags field of Elf32_Shdr: */
24
25#define SHF_MEP_VLIW 0x10000000 /* contains vliw code */
26
27#include "elf/reloc-macros.h"
28
29/* Note: The comments in this file are used by bfd/mep-relocs.pl to
30 build parts of bfd/elf32-mep.c. */
31
32/* Relocations. */
33START_RELOC_NUMBERS (elf_mep_reloc_type)
34
35 /* These two must appear first so that they are not processed by bfd/mep-relocs.pl. */
36 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_NONE, 0)
37 RELOC_NUMBER (R_RELC, 1)
38
39 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_8, 2) /* 7654 3210 U */
40 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_16, 3) /* fedc ba98 7654 3210 U */
41 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_32, 4) /* vuts rqpo nmlk jihg fedc ba98 7654 3210 U */
42
43 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_PCREL8A2, 5) /* ---- ---- 7654 321- S PC-REL */
44 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_PCREL12A2, 6) /* ---- ba98 7654 321- S PC-REL */
45 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_PCREL17A2, 7) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- gfed cba9 8765 4321 S PC-REL */
46 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_PCREL24A2, 8) /* ---- -765 4321 ---- nmlk jihg fedc ba98 S PC-REL */
47 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_PCABS24A2, 9) /* ---- -765 4321 ---- nmlk jihg fedc ba98 U */
48
49 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_LOW16, 10) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- fedc ba98 7654 3210 U no-overflow */
50 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_HI16U, 11) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- vuts rqpo nmlk jihg U no-overflow */
51 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_HI16S, 12) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- vuts rqpo nmlk jihg S no-overflow */
52 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_GPREL, 13) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- fedc ba98 7654 3210 S GP-REL*/
53 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_TPREL, 14) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- fedc ba98 7654 3210 S TP-REL*/
54
55 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_TPREL7, 15) /* ---- ---- -654 3210 U TP-REL */
56 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_TPREL7A2, 16) /* ---- ---- -654 321- U TP-REL */
57 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_TPREL7A4, 17) /* ---- ---- -654 32-- U TP-REL */
58
59 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_UIMM24, 18) /* ---- ---- 7654 3210 nmlk jihg fedc ba98 U */
60 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_ADDR24A4, 19) /* ---- ---- 7654 32-- nmlk jihg fedc ba98 U */
61
62 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_GNU_VTINHERIT, 20) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- U no-overflow */
63 RELOC_NUMBER (R_MEP_GNU_VTENTRY, 21) /* ---- ---- ---- ---- U no-overflow */
64
65END_RELOC_NUMBERS(R_MEP_max)
66
67#define EF_MEP_CPU_MASK 0xff000000 /* specific cpu bits */
68#define EF_MEP_CPU_MEP 0x00000000 /* generic MEP */
69#define EF_MEP_CPU_C2 0x01000000 /* MEP c2 */
70#define EF_MEP_CPU_C3 0x02000000 /* MEP c3 */
71#define EF_MEP_CPU_C4 0x04000000 /* MEP c4 */
72/* 5..7 are reseved */
73#define EF_MEP_CPU_C5 0x08000000 /* MEP c5 */
74#define EF_MEP_CPU_H1 0x10000000 /* MEP h1 */
75
76#define EF_MEP_COP_MASK 0x00ff0000
77#define EF_MEP_COP_NONE 0x00000000
78#define EF_MEP_COP_AVC 0x00010000
79#define EF_MEP_COP_AVC2 0x00020000
80#define EF_MEP_COP_FMAX 0x00030000
81/* 4..5 are reserved. */
82#define EF_MEP_COP_IVC2 0x00060000
83
84#define EF_MEP_LIBRARY 0x00000100 /* Built as a library */
85
86#define EF_MEP_INDEX_MASK 0x000000ff /* Configuration index */
87
88#define EF_MEP_ALL_FLAGS 0xffff01ff
89
90#endif /* _ELF_MEP_H */
